[2] Singapore
Date: Wed 11 Jul 2007
Source: ABC Radio Australia [edited]
<http://www.radioaustralia.net.au/news/stories/s1975300.htm>

Authorities in Singapore say the number of people infected with
dengue in the island state in a single week has risen to the year's
[2007] highest level.
The National Environment Agency says more than 430 cases were
reported, well above the official epidemic level.
--
