[5] Philippines (Manila)
Date: Wed 11 Jul 2007
Source: GMA News.TV [edited]
<http://www.gmanews.tv/story/50507/Dengue-cases-on-the-rise-in-Metro-Manila>

With the rainy season now here, the incidence of dengue has started
to rise, with hospitals in Metro Manila recording a marked rise in
cases.
Radio dzBB reported that the Rizal Medical Center in eastern Metro
Manila recorded 19 cases from 1-8 Jul [2007], most of the victims
being children. It said the patients include 4 who tested positive
for dengue, and a 10-year-old child with stage-2 hemorrhagic fever.
Most of the patients were from Pasig City, doctors said. Other
patients admitted at the Rizal Medical Center included residents from
Taguig, Pateros, Makati City, and Antipolo City.
Another hospital, the Amang Rodriguez Medical Center in Marikina
City, recorded at least 6 cases so far this month [July 2007].
Health authorities have warned residents to take precautions against
dengue, which they said is no longer a rainy-season disease but an
"all-year-round" disease.
They urged residents to keep their surroundings clean and to prevent
mosquitoes that carry the disease from breeding.
--
