[6] Philippines (Aklan)
Date: Fri 13 Jul 2007
Source: Philippine Information Agency [edited]
<http://www.pia.gov.ph/default.asp?m=12&fi=p070713.htm&no=65&r=&y=&mo=>

The dreaded dengue disease claimed its 1st Aklan victim on the 1st
week of July [2007] here, and cases in the province continue to rise,
bringing to a total of 78 from January [2007] to the 1st 7 days of
July of this year [2007].
Dr. Maria Magpusao, Chief of the Technical Services Division [in
Kalibo City] of the Provincial Health Office, revealed that during
the 1-7 Jul [2007] period alone, 23 cases were already reported,
while many are still coming in after the period. In June [2007], 23
cases were also reported, but the figure applies for the whole month
and not just for a week.
Dr. Magpusao said the cases may still peak in August [2007] because
it had been observed yearly that there are more cases during this
period.
[Byline: Venus G. Villanueva]
--
