[7] Philippines (Negros Occidental)
Date: Wed 11 Jul 2007
Source: News Balita [edited]
<http://news.balita.ph/index.html> (archived)

Dengue deaths climbed to 4 in Negros Occidental after the demise of a
4-year-old patient in a hospital in Sagay City Tuesday [10 Jul 2007].
But health authorities feared that the figure might be higher if
reported deaths outside of hospitals are considered.
Dr. Luisa Efren, provincial health officer said, based on Ledesma's
(Ma. Estrella Ledesma, chief of hospital of the Teresita Jalandoni
Provincial Hospital in Silay City) report [that] the 4-year-old
patient was brought to the said hospital from Sagay City, 83
kilometers (51.6 mi) north of [Sagay City].
"This brings to 4 deaths recorded so far since January this year
[2007] as dengue fever cases continue to increase in the province,"
she said. Efren said the figure could be higher than 4 if some dengue
deaths that reportedly occurred in homes were verified and recorded.
The 3 deaths previously reported were all in a barangay [district] in
Hinobaan town, 200 kilometers (124.3 mi) south of Bacolod.
Efren said Ledesma told her that from 1-7 Jul [2007] alone, there
were already 26 dengue cases at the provincial hospital. "Most of
these cases came from Victorias City," she said.
Hinobaan is one of the areas being closely monitored by the
Department of Health (DOH) central office in Manila because of an
increasing number of dengue cases.
--
