[8] American Samoa
Date: Fri 13 Jul 2007
Source: Pacific Magazine [edited]
<http://www.pacificmagazine.net/news/2007/07/13/dengue-fever-escalating-in-american-samoa>

The American Samoa Department of Health says dengue fever "appears to
be escalating" in the territory, with 22 more cases identified 2
weeks ago [30 Jun 2007].
Health officials are urging island residents to take preventive
measures and the department has also launched a media campaign to
halt the increase of dengue fever cases.
Since January this year [2007], 51 laboratory-confirmed cases of
dengue fever have been reported, the Health Department said. Of
these, 22 cases have been identified during the last 2 weeks, the
department announced in a press release.
[Byline: Fili Sagapolutele]
